						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1583 (1661 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers an endowment of money as <hi rend="italic">poliyūṭṭu</hi> by Pōtturāja Veṅgaṇan, son of Tirumalai-nāyakkar of the Nandakula-gōtra for the 6th day festival of Ādi-Brahmā and other specified provisions for the god. This is engraved over an earlier record of Kulōttuṅgachōḷa whose <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> is partly traceable on the stones. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1583 Plava, Kaṉṉi, ba. 7, Wednesday, Rōhiṇī</hi> regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1661 A.D., September 4, Wednesday, f.d.t. ·12; ·80.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
